Fortune-WWW-Postillion

Fortune-WWW-Postillion fetches fortune cookies from
http://www.der-postillon.com/search/label/Newsticker
You can either request a random cookie or give a number n and the module will
try to return the nth element of the cookie list. The number is used modulo
the number of elements in the cookie jar. So if you ask for the 5th cookie in
a 4 element jar, you will get the first one.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Fortune::WWW::Postillion

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Fortune-WWW-Postillion

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Fortune-WWW-Postillion

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Fortune-WWW-Postillion

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Fortune-WWW-Postillion/


